public class ForLoopExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // A simple for loop that prints numbers from 1 to 5
        for (int i = 1; i <= 5; i++) {
            System.out.println(i);
        }
    }
}



public class WhileLoopExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int i = 1;
        // A simple while loop that prints numbers from 1 to 5
        while (i <= 5) {
            System.out.println(i);
            i++;
        }
    }
}


//Which loop to use and when : 
1)If we know start and end condition - we use for loop
2)When we dont want know the start and end condition we use  while loop  -- use for using reading file or database 
3)Even if condition is false and we want to execute something atleast once then we will use do while loop 






